T* (Dear Billing Department,) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (I am writing on behalf of the above-referenced patient to formally dispute charges totaling $770.00 on the) Tj
T* (itemized statement dated [STATEMENT_DATE]. This dispute is submitted pursuant to 45 CFR § 149.620) Tj
T* (\(federal patient-provider dispute resolution\) and requests correction of billing errors identified through) Tj
T* (independent audit.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (The following line items are disputed:) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (1. CPT 99215 — Office Visit, High Complexity \($385.00\): The documentation provided does not support a) Tj
T* (high-complexity evaluation and management service. Based on the presenting complaint, examination scope,) Tj
T* (and medical decision-making documented, this encounter meets criteria for CPT 99213 \(moderate) Tj
T* (complexity\). This constitutes upcoding in violation of NCCI Policy Manual, Chapter 11, which requires that) Tj
T* (E/M level selection be supported by documentation of complexity elements.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (2. Modifier 25 Applied to CPT 99215 \($385.00\): Modifier 25 was appended to indicate a significant,) Tj
T* (separately identifiable E/M service on the same day as a procedure. However, the clinical documentation) Tj
T* (does not demonstrate that the E/M service was distinct from the standard pre-procedure assessment. Per) Tj
T* (NCCI Policy Manual, Chapter 1, and AMA CPT modifier 25 guidance, this modifier requires clear) Tj
T* (documentation of a separate, medically necessary evaluation beyond the procedure's inherent work.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (3. CPT 92557 — Comprehensive Audiometry \($195.00\): This service was billed at $195.00; however, the) Tj
T* (patient's coverage is governed by Washington State workers' compensation, which establishes binding) Tj
T* (maximum allowable fees. We request verification that this charge complies with the Washington L&I fee) Tj
T* (schedule as required under WAC 296-20-135 and RCW 51.04.030. If the billed amount exceeds the) Tj
T* (allowable fee, adjustment is mandatory.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (For audit integrity and transparency, the original bill has been cryptographically hashed \(SHA-256:) Tj
T* (0b6360fe23805ec38474ffd22f1a398c69172ed2e40f09a9f30636f96a265bb3\) and anchored on 0G Chain,) Tj
T* (establishing an immutable record of the disputed charges.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (We respectfully request a corrected, itemized statement reflecting these adjustments within thirty \(30\) days of) Tj
T* (receipt of this letter. Please direct all correspondence to [YOUR ADDRESS] or via the contact information) Tj
T* (on file. We remain committed to resolving this matter cooperatively and in compliance with applicable) Tj
T* (federal and state regulations.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Thank you for your prompt attention to this dispute.) Tj
